article.headline: Kennesaw St. 68, North Florida 66
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Golden Ingle hit a running jumper just inside the free-throw line with four-tenths of a second remaining in overtime to lift Kennesaw State to a 68-66 win over North Florida on Thursday night. The win capped off a Kennesaw State comeback that started with six minutes left in regulation and the Owls trailing by 11. Kennesaw State connected on four 3-point baskets in the next three minutes and pulled to within two points with 2:30 left. Ronell Wooten scored with 1:22 left to send the game to overtime tied at 60. Ingle's basket with 1:04 left in overtime gave Kennesaw State (11-15, 6-7 Atlantic Sun) a 66-65 lead. North Florida's Arnold Henry tied it with a free throw with 40 seconds remaining before Ingle came through with his winning effort. North Florida held a 36-30 point lead at halftime. Kennesaw State cut the deficit to one with just over 12 minutes to play before the Ospreys scored 10 consecutive points for a 54-43 lead. Shortly thereafter, Kennesaw State mounted its comeback. Ingle finished with 20 points. Thirteen of his points came in the first nine minutes of the game when Ingle made five of his first seven shots, three of which were beyond the 3-point line. North Florida (2-22, 0-13), dropped its 12th consecutive game. North Florida was led by James Grimball, who scored 18.
